CONNECTICUT OPINION;

Meteorology Becomes a Morality Play
LEAD: I DO not know about anyone else, but I'm getting to the point where I can't take the hassle of watching the local nightly news on television. Wars, uprisings, economic roller-coaster rides, gruesome crimes - none of that stuff pushes me over the edge. All of these things have been around since Mesopotamian days and unfortunately seem likely to continue.

In the Region: New Jersey;

For Rural Hamilton, a Commercial Spurt
LEAD: Over the last decade, Hamilton Township has steadily been changing from a farming to a suburban character as myriad housing projects have sprung up within its 40 square miles. Now, the latest sign of this Mercer County community's growth is an emerging stock of commercial space.

NATIONAL NOTEBOOK: Tulsa, Okla.;

After 5 Years, Apartments
LEAD: TULSA'S first apartment complex in five years is being built along Riverside Drive, the Arkansas River parkland corridor that connects downtown and the growing south side.

WESTCHESTER OPINION;

The Opportunities of Municipal Planning
LEAD: MUNICIPAL planning has turned into one long, continuing approval process bordering on sheer insanity. And you need not be an urban-planner or architect to realize it.
